<node CREATED="1738336919486" MODIFIED="1738336919486" TEXT="Background        Before 1835, Indian education was mainly in Persian, Sanskrit &amp; regional languages. British debated between Orientalists (supporting traditional education) and Anglicists (favoring English-based education)."/>
<node CREATED="1738336928463" MODIFIED="1738336928463" TEXT="Concept        Lord Macaulay&#x2019;s Minute (1835) argued for English as the medium of instruction to create a class of English-educated Indians who could assist in British admin"/>
<node CREATED="1738336935191" MODIFIED="1738336935191" TEXT="Aims        Spread Western knowledge, Train Indians for administrative roles, Replace Persian &amp; Sanskrit with English, Create a Westernized elite"/>
<node CREATED="1738336942191" MODIFIED="1738336942191" TEXT="Characteristics        English became official medium in schools, Focus on Western literature, science, and law, Decline of indigenous education systems"/>
<node CREATED="1738336949151" MODIFIED="1738336949151" TEXT="Subjects Taught        English language, Western philosophy, Science, Law, Mathematics, Limited focus on Indian history &amp; culture"/>
<node CREATED="1738336956263" MODIFIED="1738336956263" TEXT="Method of Teaching        Textbook-based, Lecture method, Examination system, Emphasis on rote learning &amp; clerical skills"/>
<node CREATED="1738336963615" MODIFIED="1738336963615" TEXT="Role of Teacher        British-trained teachers, Focused on imparting Western knowledge, Discouraged traditional learning"/>
<node CREATED="1738336969919" MODIFIED="1738336969919" TEXT="Student Life        Shift from Gurukuls, Madrasas, and Tols to British-style schools, Education linked to government jobs"/>
<node CREATED="1738336976783" MODIFIED="1738336976783" TEXT="Impact on Indian Education        Decline of indigenous institutions, Growth of English-medium schools, Creation of a Western-educated elite"/>
<node CREATED="1738336982743" MODIFIED="1738336982743" TEXT="Criticism        Ignored Indian knowledge systems, Created cultural alienation, Education was elitist (benefiting only upper-class Indians)"/>
<node CREATED="1738336989351" MODIFIED="1738336989351" TEXT="Influence on Modern Ed.        Foundation of the modern Indian education system, Led to universities (Calcutta, Bombay, Madras &#x2013; 1857), English remains dominant in Indian education today"/>
</node>
