<node CREATED="1738337054815" MODIFIED="1738337054815" TEXT="Background        After Macaulay&#x2019;s Minute (1835), English education spread, but it lacked proper structure. The British East India Company sought reforms. Charles Wood, the President of the Board of Control, issued the Wood&#x2019;s Dispatch in 1854, often called the &#x201c;Magna Carta of Indian Education&#x201d;."/>
<node CREATED="1738337064560" MODIFIED="1738337064560" TEXT="Concept        Aimed to establish a structured education system in India with a focus on Western knowledge, vocational training, and mass ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738337072183" MODIFIED="1738337072183" TEXT="Aims        Education for administration, Spread of Western knowledge, Promotion of Indian languages, Vocational education, Women&#x2019;s education, Teacher training"/>
<node CREATED="1738337078695" MODIFIED="1738337078695" TEXT="Characteristics        Hierarchical system (Primary, Secondary, and Higher Education), English as the medium for higher studies but support for vernacular languages at lower levels"/>
<node CREATED="1738337086183" MODIFIED="1738337086183" TEXT="Subjects Taught        Western sciences, Literature, Law, Engineering, Medicine, Vocational skills, Encouragement of moral &amp; religious ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738337146487" MODIFIED="1738337146487" TEXT="Method of Teaching        Classroom-based, Examinations, Vocational training, Teacher training institutes, Focus on practical ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738337238160" MODIFIED="1738337238160" TEXT="Role of Teacher        Need for qualified teachers, Introduction of teacher training institutions, Salaries &amp; working conditions improved"/>
<node CREATED="1738337244498" MODIFIED="1738337244498" TEXT="Student Life        More schools &amp; colleges opened, Introduction of scholarships, Expansion of education for women and lower castes"/>
<node CREATED="1738337252443" MODIFIED="1738337252443" TEXT="Impact on Indian Education        Foundation of modern education system, Creation of universities (Calcutta, Bombay, Madras - 1857), Increased British control over ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738337259611" MODIFIED="1738337259611" TEXT="Criticism        Focused on producing clerks for administration, Western bias in curriculum, Education remained elitist &amp; urban-focused"/>
<node CREATED="1738337271695" MODIFIED="1738337271695" TEXT="Influence on Modern Ed.        Laid the foundation of university education in India, Encouraged technical &amp; vocational education, Strengthened teacher training &amp; women&#x2019;s ed"/>
</node>
