<node CREATED="1738338082116" MODIFIED="1738338082116" TEXT="Background        The National Education Movement emerged as a response to British colonial education policies, especially after the Partition of Bengal (1905). Indians sought an independent education system that promoted nationalism, indigenous culture, and self-reliance."/>
<node CREATED="1738338090114" MODIFIED="1738338090114" TEXT="Concept        Aimed to establish an alternative education system based on Indian values, Swadeshi ideals, and nationalistic spirit, free from British control."/>
<node CREATED="1738338098578" MODIFIED="1738338098578" TEXT="Aims        Promote Indian culture &amp; heritage, Reduce dependence on British education, Spread Swadeshi spirit, Focus on vernacular languages, Provide mass ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738338114426" MODIFIED="1738338114426" TEXT="Characteristics        Establishment of national schools &amp; universities, Emphasis on Indian history, culture, and self-reliance, Medium of instruction in vernacular lang"/>
<node CREATED="1738338122162" ID="ID_1864407296" MODIFIED="1738338122162" TEXT="Subjects Taught        Indian philosophy, History, Science, Agriculture, Handicrafts, Swadeshi movement, Less emphasis on British curr"/>
<node CREATED="1738338133179" MODIFIED="1738338133179" TEXT="Method of Teaching        Practical education, Gurukul system revival, Skill-based training, Moral &amp; value education, Opposed rote learning"/>
<node CREATED="1738338140129" MODIFIED="1738338140129" TEXT="Role of Teacher        Teachers acted as nationalist leaders, Promoted self-reliance &amp; patriotism, Focused on moral ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738338147378" MODIFIED="1738338147378" TEXT="Student Life        Increased student participation in freedom movements, Growth of non-British schools &amp; colleges, Rise in Swadeshi education institutions"/>
<node CREATED="1738338159978" ID="ID_1420893859" MODIFIED="1738338159978" TEXT="Impact on Indian Education        Establishment of Banaras Hindu University (1916), Jamia Millia Islamia (1920), Visva-Bharati (1921), Strengthened Indian identity in ed"/>
<node CREATED="1738338167560" ID="ID_1306265445" MODIFIED="1738338167560" TEXT="Criticism        Lacked government recognition, Faced financial difficulties, Limited reach to rural ar"/>
<node CREATED="1738338176273" MODIFIED="1738338176273" TEXT="Influence on Modern Ed.        Inspired Gandhian education model (Nai Talim), Paved way for Indianized curriculum post-independence, Strengthened vernacular ed"/>
</node>
